            <biogHist>
                <p>Margaret or Mairearad MacLeod was born to John MacLeod, crofter, and Mary MacLeod
                    n√©e MacLean and at the time of the 1851 census she was living in Haclait,
                    Benbecula. There is no record of her ever marrying. She worked as a crofter or
                    cottar throughout her life, dying a pauper at the age of 85 in Liniclate, a
                    short distance from Haclait. </p>
                <p>Margaret is mentioned in the notebooks in a note Carmichael made to visit her for
